snippet.textDisplay:
The singing from 1:39 to 2:08 is live, as is the singing from 2:35 to 3:55. The vocalizations at these points are different to the single recording.

However, the rest of it sounds exactly like the single, even down to the mixing, orchestra, guitar and whatever else Zimmer is pretending to play. I love the song and I am a long-time fan of Hans Zimmer, but this is a curious mix of pre-record and live performance. Perhaps Billie's cold from her time performing at the Oscars was still an issue here, hence them using a backing track for most of the song? But anyone with Audacity can bring in the single release version and the audio of this recording, adjust the levels to balance them out, and easily hear/compare the differences and similarities between the two recordings.

I love the song but I'd love to hear a truly, 100% live version.

However, the rest of it sounds exactly like the single, even down to the mixing, orchestra, guitar and whatever else Zimmer is pretending to play. I love the song and I am a long-time fan of Hans Zimmer, but this is a curious mix of pre-record and live performance. Perhaps Billie's cold from her time performing at the Oscars was still an issue here, hence them using a backing track for most of the song? But anyone with Audacity can bring in the single release version and the audio of this recording, adjust the levels to balance them out, and easily hear/compare the differences and similarities between the two recordings.

I love the song but I'd love to hear a truly, 100% live version.
